{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":759,"text":"So we all have our own biases."},{"time":3133,"text":"For example, some of us tend to think"},{"time":5808,"text":"that it's very difficult to transform\nfailing government systems."},{"time":9871,"text":"When we think of government systems,"},{"time":11642,"text":"we tend to think that they're archaic,\nset in their ways,"},{"time":15257,"text":"and perhaps, the leadership\nis just too bureaucratic"},{"time":17977,"text":"to be able to change things."},{"time":20097,"text":"Well, today, I want\nto challenge that theory."},{"time":23886,"text":"I want to tell you a story\nof a very large government system"},{"time":27979,"text":"that has not only put itself\non the path of reform"},{"time":31447,"text":"but has also shown\nfairly spectacular results"},{"time":34660,"text":"in less than three years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36746,"text":"This is what a classroom\nin a public school in India looks like."},{"time":41050,"text":"There are 1 million such schools in India."},{"time":43878,"text":"And even for me,\nwho's lived in India all her life,"},{"time":47034,"text":"walking into one of these schools\nis fairly heartbreaking."},{"time":51106,"text":"By the time kids are 11,"},{"time":53199,"text":"50 percent of them have fallen\nso far behind in their education"},{"time":57255,"text":"that they have no hope to recover."},{"time":59606,"text":"11-year-olds cannot do simple addition,"},{"time":62428,"text":"they cannot construct\na grammatically correct sentence."},{"time":65779,"text":"These are things that you and I\nwould expect an 8-year-old"},{"time":69066,"text":"to be able to do."},{"time":70672,"text":"By the time kids are 13 or 14,"},{"time":73493,"text":"they tend to drop out of schools."},{"time":76313,"text":"In India, public schools\nnot only offer free education --"},{"time":79611,"text":"they offer free textbooks,\nfree workbooks, free meals,"},{"time":83048,"text":"sometimes even cash scholarships."},{"time":85691,"text":"And yet, 40 percent of the parents today"},{"time":88700,"text":"are choosing to pull their children\nout of public schools"},{"time":91904,"text":"and pay out of their pockets\nto put them in private schools."},{"time":95445,"text":"As a comparison,\nin a far richer country, the US,"},{"time":99134,"text":"that number is only 10 percent."},{"time":101377,"text":"That's a huge statement on how broken\nthe Indian public education system is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107431,"text":"So it was with that background\nthat I got a call in the summer of 2013"},{"time":111931,"text":"from an absolutely brilliant lady\ncalled Surina Rajan."},{"time":115778,"text":"She was, at that time, the head\nof the Department of School Education"},{"time":119919,"text":"in a state called Haryana in India."},{"time":122209,"text":"So she said to us, \"Look, I've been\nheading this department"},{"time":125304,"text":"for the last two years."},{"time":126554,"text":"I've tried a number of things,\nand nothing seems to work."},{"time":130008,"text":"Can you possibly help?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":132852,"text":"Let me describe Haryana\na little bit to you."},{"time":135690,"text":"Haryana is a state\nwhich has 30 million people."},{"time":139721,"text":"It has 15,000 public schools"},{"time":142916,"text":"and 2 million plus\nchildren in those public schools."},{"time":146119,"text":"So basically, with that phone call,"},{"time":148587,"text":"I promised to help a state and system"},{"time":151033,"text":"which was as large as that of Peru\nor Canada transform itself."},{"time":156591,"text":"As I started this project,\nI was very painfully aware of two things."},{"time":160192,"text":"One, that I had never done\nanything like this before."},{"time":163427,"text":"And two, many others had,\nperhaps without too much success."},{"time":168247,"text":"As my colleagues and I\nlooked across the country"},{"time":171033,"text":"and across the world,"},{"time":172365,"text":"we couldn't find another example"},{"time":174257,"text":"that we could just pick up\nand replicate in Haryana."},{"time":177107,"text":"We knew that we had to craft\nour own journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180692,"text":"But anyway, we jumped right in\nand as we jumped in,"},{"time":183770,"text":"all sorts of ideas started flying at us."},{"time":186533,"text":"People said, \"Let's change\nthe way we recruit teachers,"},{"time":189595,"text":"let's hire new principals and train them"},{"time":192363,"text":"and send them on international\nlearning tours,"},{"time":194605,"text":"let's put technology inside classrooms.\""},{"time":197128,"text":"By the end of week one,\nwe had 50 ideas on the table,"},{"time":199758,"text":"all amazing, all sounded right."},{"time":202010,"text":"There was no way we were\ngoing to be able to implement 50 things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207103,"text":"So I said, \"Hang on, stop."},{"time":209175,"text":"Let's first at least decide\nwhat is it we're trying to achieve.\""},{"time":212448,"text":"So with a lot of push and pull and debate,"},{"time":215246,"text":"Haryana set itself a goal\nwhich said: by 2020,"},{"time":219157,"text":"we want 80 percent of our children\nto be at grade-level knowledge."},{"time":223590,"text":"Now the specifics of the goal\ndon't matter here,"},{"time":226497,"text":"but what matters\nis how specific the goal is."},{"time":229786,"text":"Because it really allowed us\nto take all those ideas"},{"time":232782,"text":"which were being thrown at us"},{"time":234231,"text":"and say which ones\nwe were going to implement."},{"time":236629,"text":"Does this idea support this goal?\nIf yes, let's keep it."},{"time":240972,"text":"But if it doesn't or we're not sure,\nthen let's put it aside."},{"time":244276,"text":"As simple as it sounds,\nhaving a very specific goal right up front"},{"time":248924,"text":"has really allowed us to be\nvery sharp and focused"},{"time":252164,"text":"in our transformation journey."},{"time":253816,"text":"And looking back over\nthe last two and a half years,"},{"time":256458,"text":"that has been a huge positive for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259488,"text":"So we had the goal,"},{"time":260676,"text":"and now we needed to figure out\nwhat are the issues, what is broken."},{"time":265001,"text":"Before we went into schools,\na lot of people told us"},{"time":267752,"text":"that education quality is poor"},{"time":269842,"text":"because either the teachers are lazy,\nthey don't come into schools,"},{"time":273740,"text":"or they're incapable,\nthey actually don't know how to teach."},{"time":277427,"text":"Well, when we went inside schools,\nwe found something completely different."},{"time":281734,"text":"On most days, most teachers\nwere actually inside schools."},{"time":285771,"text":"And when you spoke with them,"},{"time":287374,"text":"you realized they were perfectly capable\nof teaching elementary classes."},{"time":291952,"text":"But they were not teaching."},{"time":294702,"text":"I went to a school"},{"time":296125,"text":"where the teachers were getting\nthe construction of a classroom"},{"time":299233,"text":"and a toilet supervised."},{"time":301645,"text":"I went to another school"},{"time":303311,"text":"where two of the teachers\nhad gone to a nearby bank branch"},{"time":306226,"text":"to deposit scholarship money\ninto kids' accounts."},{"time":309452,"text":"At lunchtime, most teachers\nwere spending all of their time"},{"time":313767,"text":"getting the midday meal cooking,\nsupervised and served to the students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318907,"text":"So we asked the teachers,"},{"time":320135,"text":"\"What's going on,\nwhy are you not teaching?\""},{"time":323196,"text":"And they said, \"This is\nwhat's expected of us."},{"time":326500,"text":"When a supervisor comes to visit us,"},{"time":328835,"text":"these are exactly the things\nthat he checks."},{"time":331248,"text":"Has the toilet been made,\nhas the meal been served."},{"time":333952,"text":"When my principal\ngoes to a meeting at headquarters,"},{"time":337086,"text":"these are exactly the things\nwhich are discussed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":340481,"text":"You see, what had happened was,\nover the last two decades,"},{"time":344529,"text":"India had been fighting the challenge\nof access, having enough schools,"},{"time":348383,"text":"and enrollment, bringing children\ninto the schools."},{"time":351178,"text":"So the government\nlaunched a whole host of programs"},{"time":354632,"text":"to address these challenges,"},{"time":356515,"text":"and the teachers became\nthe implicit executors of these programs."},{"time":361296,"text":"Not explicitly, but implicitly."},{"time":364652,"text":"And now, what was actually needed\nwas not to actually train teachers further"},{"time":369692,"text":"or to monitor their attendance"},{"time":371615,"text":"but to tell them\nthat what is most important"},{"time":375510,"text":"is for them to go back\ninside classrooms and teach."},{"time":378134,"text":"They needed to be monitored\nand measured and awarded"},{"time":382012,"text":"on the quality of teaching"},{"time":383384,"text":"and not on all sorts of other things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386018,"text":"So as we went through\nthe education system,"},{"time":388502,"text":"as we delved into it deeper,\nwe found a few such core root causes"},{"time":393786,"text":"which were determining, which were\nshaping how people behaved in the system."},{"time":397942,"text":"And we realized that unless we change\nthose specific things,"},{"time":401649,"text":"we could do a number of other things."},{"time":403626,"text":"We could train, we could put\ntechnology into schools,"},{"time":406493,"text":"but the system wouldn't change."},{"time":408497,"text":"And addressing these non-obvious\ncore issues"},{"time":411578,"text":"became a key part of the program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414678,"text":"So, we had the goal and we had the issues,"},{"time":417654,"text":"and now we needed to figure out\nwhat the solutions were."},{"time":420888,"text":"We obviously did not want\nto recreate the wheel,"},{"time":423350,"text":"so we said, \"Let's look around\nand see what we can find.\""},{"time":426490,"text":"And we found these beautiful,\nsmall pilot experiments"},{"time":431411,"text":"all over the country\nand all over the world."},{"time":434146,"text":"Small things being done by NGOs,\nbeing done by foundations."},{"time":438138,"text":"But what was also interesting\nwas that none of them actually scaled."},{"time":442119,"text":"All of them were limited\nto 50, 100 or 500 schools."},{"time":445681,"text":"And here, we were looking\nfor a solution for 15,000 schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449180,"text":"So we looked into why,"},{"time":450908,"text":"if these things actually work,\nwhy don't they actually scale?"},{"time":454572,"text":"What happens is that\nwhen a typical NGO comes in,"},{"time":457831,"text":"they not only bring in their expertise"},{"time":460268,"text":"but they also bring in\nadditional resources."},{"time":462807,"text":"So they might bring in money,"},{"time":464588,"text":"they might bring in people,"},{"time":465933,"text":"they might bring in technology."},{"time":467651,"text":"And in the 50 or 100 schools\nthat they actually operate in,"},{"time":472064,"text":"those additional resources\nactually create a difference."},{"time":475476,"text":"But now imagine that the head of this NGO"},{"time":478032,"text":"goes to the head\nof the School Education Department"},{"time":480811,"text":"and says, \"Hey, now let's do this\nfor 15,000 schools.\""},{"time":484100,"text":"Where is that guy or girl\ngoing to find the money"},{"time":487577,"text":"to actually scale this up\nto 15,000 schools?"},{"time":490305,"text":"He doesn't have the additional money,"},{"time":492091,"text":"he doesn't have the resources."},{"time":493712,"text":"And hence, innovations don't scale."},{"time":496938,"text":"So right at the beginning\nof the project, what we said was,"},{"time":500365,"text":"\"Whatever we have to do\nhas to be scalable,"},{"time":503035,"text":"it has to work in all 15,000 schools.\""},{"time":506346,"text":"And hence, it has to work\nwithin the existing budgets"},{"time":510162,"text":"and resources that the state actually has."},{"time":513552,"text":"Much easier said than done."},{"time":515451,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516864,"text":"I think this was definitely\nthe point in time"},{"time":519044,"text":"when my team hated me."},{"time":520912,"text":"We spent a lot of long hours\nin office, in cafés,"},{"time":526114,"text":"sometimes even in bars,"},{"time":527433,"text":"scratching out heads and saying,"},{"time":529120,"text":"\"Where are the solutions,\nhow are we going to solve this problem?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":532410,"text":"In the end, I think we did\nfind solutions to many of the issues."},{"time":536214,"text":"I'll give you an example."},{"time":538111,"text":"In the context of effective learning,"},{"time":540077,"text":"one of the things people talk about\nis hands-on learning."},{"time":543386,"text":"Children shouldn't memorize\nthings from books,"},{"time":545678,"text":"they should do activities,"},{"time":547291,"text":"and that's a more effective way to learn."},{"time":549314,"text":"Which basically means\ngiving students things"},{"time":551636,"text":"like beads, learning rods, abacuses."},{"time":555082,"text":"But we did not have\nthe budgets to give that"},{"time":557560,"text":"to 15,000 schools, 2 million children."},{"time":560199,"text":"We needed another solution."},{"time":562446,"text":"We couldn't think of anything."},{"time":564368,"text":"One day, one of our team members\nwent to a school"},{"time":567221,"text":"and saw a teacher pick up sticks\nand stones from the garden outside"},{"time":571611,"text":"and take them into the classroom"},{"time":573456,"text":"and give them to the students."},{"time":575726,"text":"That was a huge eureka moment for us."},{"time":579617,"text":"So what happens now\nin the textbooks in Haryana"},{"time":582524,"text":"is that after every concept,\nwe have a little box"},{"time":585290,"text":"which are instructions\nfor the teachers which say,"},{"time":587702,"text":"\"To teach this concept,\nhere's an activity that you can do."},{"time":591882,"text":"And by the way, in order\nto actually do this activity,"},{"time":594993,"text":"here are things that you can use\nfrom your immediate environment,"},{"time":598196,"text":"whether it be the garden outside\nor the classroom inside,"},{"time":601241,"text":"which can be used\nas learning aids for kids.\""},{"time":604194,"text":"And we see teachers all over Haryana"},{"time":606664,"text":"using lots of innovative things\nto be able to teach students."},{"time":610617,"text":"So in this way, whatever we designed,"},{"time":614226,"text":"we were actually able to implement it"},{"time":616328,"text":"across all 15,000 schools from day one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620304,"text":"Now, this brings me to my last point."},{"time":622514,"text":"How do you implement something\nacross 15,000 schools"},{"time":625811,"text":"and 100,000 teachers?"},{"time":628357,"text":"The department used to have a process"},{"time":630403,"text":"which is very interesting."},{"time":631701,"text":"I like to call it \"The Chain of Hope.\""},{"time":636240,"text":"They would write a letter\nfrom the headquarters"},{"time":638624,"text":"and send it to the next level,"},{"time":640273,"text":"which was the district offices."},{"time":642186,"text":"They would hope that in each\nof these district offices,"},{"time":644867,"text":"an officer would get the letter,\nwould open it, read it"},{"time":648866,"text":"and then forward it to the next level,"},{"time":650984,"text":"which was the block offices."},{"time":653015,"text":"And then you would hope\nthat at the block office,"},{"time":656804,"text":"somebody else got the letter,"},{"time":658311,"text":"opened it, read it and forwarded it\neventually to the 15,000 principals."},{"time":662354,"text":"And then one would hope\nthat the principals"},{"time":665037,"text":"got the letter, received it,\nunderstood it"},{"time":667708,"text":"and started implementing it."},{"time":669662,"text":"It was a little bit ridiculous."},{"time":672684,"text":"Now, we knew technology was the answer,"},{"time":675169,"text":"but we also knew\nthat most of these schools"},{"time":677334,"text":"don't have a computer or email."},{"time":680497,"text":"However, what the teachers do have\nare smartphones."},{"time":683604,"text":"They're constantly on SMS,\non Facebook and on WhatsApp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688650,"text":"So what now happens in Haryana is,"},{"time":690919,"text":"all principals and teachers are divided\ninto hundreds of WhatsApp groups"},{"time":695563,"text":"and anytime something needs\nto be communicated,"},{"time":698409,"text":"it's just posted across\nall WhatsApp groups."},{"time":701486,"text":"It spreads like wildfire."},{"time":703711,"text":"You can immediately check\nwho has received it,"},{"time":706728,"text":"who has read it."},{"time":708042,"text":"Teachers can ask clarification\nquestions instantaneously."},{"time":711926,"text":"And what's interesting is,"},{"time":713191,"text":"it's not just the headquarters\nwho are answering these questions."},{"time":716573,"text":"Another teacher from\na completely different part of the state"},{"time":719486,"text":"will stand up and answer the question."},{"time":721903,"text":"Everybody's acting\nas everybody's peer group,"},{"time":724607,"text":"and things are getting implemented."},{"time":727784,"text":"So today, when you go\nto a school in Haryana,"},{"time":730091,"text":"things look different."},{"time":731702,"text":"The teachers are back inside classrooms,"},{"time":734156,"text":"they're teaching."},{"time":735484,"text":"Often with innovative techniques."},{"time":737740,"text":"When a supervisor\ncomes to visit the classroom,"},{"time":740866,"text":"he or she not only checks\nthe construction of the toilet"},{"time":744757,"text":"but also what is the quality of teaching."},{"time":748092,"text":"Once a quarter,\nall students across the state"},{"time":751232,"text":"are assessed on their learning outcomes"},{"time":753421,"text":"and schools which are\ndoing well are rewarded."},{"time":756303,"text":"And schools which are not doing so well"},{"time":758796,"text":"find themselves having\ndifficult conversations."},{"time":761568,"text":"Of course, they also get\nadditional support"},{"time":763671,"text":"to be able to do better in the future."},{"time":767232,"text":"In the context of education,"},{"time":768880,"text":"it's very difficult\nto see results quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771630,"text":"When people talk about systemic,\nlarge-scale change,"},{"time":774629,"text":"they talk about periods\nof 7 years and 10 years."},{"time":778232,"text":"But not in Haryana."},{"time":780153,"text":"In the last one year, there have been\nthree independent studies,"},{"time":784129,"text":"all measuring student learning outcomes,"},{"time":786732,"text":"which indicate that something fundamental,"},{"time":789063,"text":"something unique is happening in Haryana."},{"time":791622,"text":"Learning levels of children\nhave stopped declining,"},{"time":794654,"text":"and they have started going up."},{"time":796481,"text":"Haryana is one of the few\nstates in the country"},{"time":799715,"text":"which is showing an improvement,"},{"time":801318,"text":"and certainly the one that is showing\nthe fastest rate of improvement."},{"time":806005,"text":"These are still early signs,"},{"time":807397,"text":"there's a long way to go,"},{"time":808615,"text":"but this gives us a lot of hope\nfor the future."},{"time":812859,"text":"I recently went to a school,"},{"time":814446,"text":"and as I was leaving,"},{"time":816413,"text":"I ran into a lady,"},{"time":817588,"text":"her name was Parvati,"},{"time":818763,"text":"she was the mother of a child,"},{"time":820225,"text":"and she was smiling."},{"time":821828,"text":"And I said, \"Why are you smiling,\nwhat's going on?\""},{"time":824761,"text":"And she said, \"I don't know\nwhat's going on,"},{"time":827531,"text":"but what I do know\nis that my children are learning,"},{"time":830642,"text":"they're having fun,"},{"time":832117,"text":"and for the time being, I'll stop\nmy search for a private school"},{"time":835336,"text":"to send them to.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":837523,"text":"So I go back to where I started:"},{"time":839547,"text":"Can government systems transform?"},{"time":842163,"text":"I certainly believe so."},{"time":843687,"text":"I think if you give them the right levers,"},{"time":845805,"text":"they can move mountains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847735,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848910,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}